# Testing Standards

## Test Organization
- Group tests by functionality
- Use test classes for related tests
- Use test modules for related test classes
- Follow project structure in test structure
- Use meaningful test names

## Test Quality
- Tests should be:
  - Fast
  - Independent
  - Repeatable
  - Self-validating
  - Timely
- Avoid test interdependence
- Avoid test order dependence
- Clean up after tests

## Assertions
- Use specific assertions
- Include meaningful messages
- Test both positive and negative cases
- Test boundary conditions
- Test error conditions

## Test Environment
- Use virtual environments
- Use test configuration
- Use test databases
- Use test file system
- Use test network settings

## Performance Testing
- Test response times
- Test resource usage
- Test scalability
- Test under load
- Test concurrent operations

## Security Testing
- Test authentication
- Test authorization
- Test input validation
- Test data encryption
- Test secure communication

## UI Testing
- Test user interactions
- Test responsive design
- Test accessibility
- Test cross-browser compatibility
- Test error messages

## API Testing
- Test endpoints
- Test request/response formats
- Test error handling
- Test rate limiting
- Test authentication

## Documentation
- Document test setup
- Document test data
- Document test environment
- Document test dependencies
- Document test results
